    {
      "segments": [
        {
          "scid": "sn22.22:1.1",
          "pli": "Sāvatthiyaṃ … tatra kho … ",
          "en": "At Sāvatthī. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn22.22:1.2",
          "pli": "“bhārañca vo, bhikkhave, desessāmi bhārahārañca bhārādānañca bhāranikkhepanañca. ",
          "en": "“Mendicants, I will teach you the burden, the bearer of the burden, the picking up of the burden, and the putting down of the burden. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn22.22:1.3",
          "pli": "Taṃ suṇātha. ",
          "en": "Listen … "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn22.22:1.4",
          "pli": "Katamo ca, bhikkhave, bhāro? ",
          "en": "And what is the burden? "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn22.22:1.5",
          "pli": "Pañcupādānakkhandhā tissa vacanīyaṃ. ",
          "en": "The five grasping aggregates, it should be said. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn22.22:1.6",
          "pli": "Katame pañca? ",
          "en": "What five? "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn22.22:1.7",
          "pli": "Rūpupādānakkhandho, vedanupādānakkhandho, saññupādānakkhandho, saṅkhārupādānakkhandho, viññāṇupādānakkhandho; ",
          "en": "The grasping aggregates of form, feeling, perception, choices, and consciousness. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn22.22:1.8",
          "pli": "ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, bhāro. ",
          "en": "This is called the burden. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn22.22:2.1",
          "pli": "Katamo ca, bhikkhave, bhārahāro? ",
          "en": "And who is the bearer of the burden? "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn22.22:2.2",
          "pli": "Puggalo tissa vacanīyaṃ. ",
          "en": "The person, it should be said; "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn22.22:2.3",
          "pli": "Yvāyaṃ āyasmā evaṃnāmo evaṅgotto; ",
          "en": "the venerable of such and such name and clan. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn22.22:2.4",
          "pli": "ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, bhārahāro. ",
          "en": "This is called the bearer of the burden. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn22.22:3.1",
          "pli": "Katamañca, bhikkhave, bhārādānaṃ? ",
          "en": "And what is the picking up of the burden? "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn22.22:3.2",
          "pli": "Yāyaṃ taṇhā ponobhavikā nandīrāgasahagatā tatratatrābhinandinī, seyyathidaṃ—",
          "en": "It’s the craving that leads to future lives, mixed up with relishing and greed, taking pleasure in various different realms. That is, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn22.22:3.3",
          "pli": "kāmataṇhā, bhavataṇhā, vibhavataṇhā. ",
          "en": "craving for sensual pleasures, craving to continue existence, and craving to end existence. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn22.22:3.4",
          "pli": "Idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, bhārādānaṃ. ",
          "en": "This is called the picking up of the burden. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn22.22:4.1",
          "pli": "Katamañca, bhikkhave, bhāranikkhepanaṃ? ",
          "en": "And what is the putting down of the burden? "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn22.22:4.2",
          "pli": "Yo tassāyeva taṇhāya asesavirāganirodho cāgo paṭinissaggo mutti anālayo. ",
          "en": "It’s the fading away and cessation of that very same craving with nothing left over; giving it away, letting it go, releasing it, and not adhering to it. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn22.22:4.3",
          "pli": "Idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, bhāranikkhepanan”ti. ",
          "en": "This is called the putting down of the burden.” "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn22.22:5.1",
          "pli": "Idamavoca bhagavā. ",
          "en": "That is what the Buddha said. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn22.22:5.2",
          "pli": "Idaṃ vatvāna sugato athāparaṃ etadavoca satthā: ",
          "en": "Then the Holy One, the Teacher, went on to say: "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn22.22:6.1",
          "pli": "“Bhārā have pañcakkhandhā, ",
          "en": "“The five aggregates are indeed burdens, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn22.22:6.2",
          "pli": "bhārahāro ca puggalo; ",
          "en": "and the person is the bearer of the burden. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn22.22:6.3",
          "pli": "Bhārādānaṃ dukhaṃ loke, ",
          "en": "Picking up the burden is suffering in the world, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn22.22:6.4",
          "pli": "bhāranikkhepanaṃ sukhaṃ. ",
          "en": "and putting the burden down is happiness. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn22.22:7.1",
          "pli": "Nikkhipitvā garuṃ bhāraṃ, ",
          "en": "When the heavy burden is put down "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn22.22:7.2",
          "pli": "aññaṃ bhāraṃ anādiya; ",
          "en": "without picking up another, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn22.22:7.3",
          "pli": "Samūlaṃ taṇhamabbuyha, ",
          "en": "and craving’s pulled out from the root, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn22.22:7.4",
          "pli": "nicchāto parinibbuto”ti. ",
          "en": "you’re hungerless, extinguished.” "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn22.22:7.5",
          "pli": "Paṭhamaṃ. ",
          "en": ""
        }
      ],
